ge best practices with one another. Your role will be to facilitate ongoing discussion with the COP. \n<br /> \n<br />The &quot;Partners Community of Practice&quot; is managed on Slack and consists of Partners who are selling their own consulting services in conjunction with IdeaScale software to support innovation at large scale organizations. The purpose of the Partners COP is to provide a place for the exchange of best practices for pitching an idea and innovation management solution such as our own. Your role will be to regularly post resources and insights to this Slack-based community. \n<br /> \n<br />Your professional opportunity and learning opportunity: \n<br />In this role, you will have the opportunity to experiment with techniques in engaging a crowd on social platforms (slack and IdeaScale, and possibly twitter and LinkedIn). We encourage you to chat with the team, review customer data, and do other research to know your audience. Through research and experimentation, you will gain skill and experience and the evidence to demonstrate your learnings and success. \n<br /> \n<br />We will track specific success metrics in conjunction with your role as COP manager and facilitator, so that you can readily report on your successes and wins at the conclusion of the internship. \n<br /> \n<br />Part of the role of the COP manager will also be to review, curate, and classify our rich data base of resources and to assist with customer roundtable discussions. You will also have opportunities to write blog entries, build infographics, post on social media, and create video content on innovation topics for building your own personal brand and portfolio of work in the field of innovation and entrepreneurship. \n<br /> \n<br />Note: start and end dates are flexible and can be set at time of interview.<h3>Responsibilities</h3> - Manage the &quot;Innovation Management Community of Practice&quot;. Keep content current and facilitate discussion \n<br />- Manage the &quot