r countries habitually in conflict with their adversaries to transcend their differences and become powerfully related and aligned with each other for their mutual benefit. \n<br /> \n<br />With the successful development of ontology based programs, it is possible today for foreign policymakers and other key government officials to effectively diminish the issues that stand between them and their adversaries. \n<br /> \n<br />Through the various ontology based programs that focus on communication, diplomatic solutions will be many times more effective than ever before. This means that millions of lives can be spared the misery of armed conflicts, the destruction of cities, becoming refugees, the abuse of human rights and end decades of hostility. \n<br /> \n<br />Among the various benefits of ontology based programs, the processes used dramatically expands the participant\'s level of conscious awareness. This is extremely important because it makes it possible for the official participants to accurately identify what would be necessary to produce unprecedented breakthrough results. \n<br /> \n<br />The officials would become able to recognize critical issues bypassed or misconstrued that continually undermine the effectiveness of policies, negotiations and strategies. \n<br /> \n<br />The programs have been used with consistent and outstanding success worldwide in corporations, non-profits and select government agencies since the 1970s. \n<br /><h3>Responsibilities</h3> Our Program Associates are assigned to one of the following positions……… \n<br /> \n<br />1-Program Associates research the officials of assigned governments and multilateral institutions. They call officials to share information about the breakthrough programs we advocate. Those based in New York, Washington or other world capitals may also meet with officials depending on project needs. \n<br /> \n<br />2-Other Program Associates research potential donors, foreign policy experts, former military leaders, counter-terrorism experts and others. \n<br /> \n<br />3-Program Associates work on our Young Diplomat Project. The Young Diplomat Project connects high school Social Studies and World History Students with high ranking diplomats at the UN Secretariat, the Permanent Missions of UN Member States in New York, at the State Department and Embassies in Washington.<h2>Requirements</h2> 1-Applicants must speak fluent English. Note: For us fluent English means you can be easily understood without repeating yourself. \n<br /> \n<br />2-We require that team members honor all their promises and agreements with us very carefully. \n<br /> \n<br />3-Team members are required to remain on our team for 3 months. \n<br /> \n<br />4-This position is for applicants with resumes that reflect education in international relations, political science, public service, foreign service, diplomacy, conflict resolution, counter-terrorism, human rights, national security, global studies, government, Middle East studies, Asian studies, African and European studies, peace studies, environmental studies and other closely related subjects. \n<br /> \n<br />5-If the applicant’s studies do not fit the list above, they may write to us explaining the reasons why they feel they would be a good candidate for the position. \n<br /> \n<br /> \n<br />','Program Associate-Foreign Relations Breakthrough Project-AK-4-6-18','','publish','closed','closed','','program-associate-foreign-relations-breakthrough-project-ak-4-6-18','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1460',0,'noo_job','',0),(1461,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Organization for International Cooperation','Organization for International Cooperation','','publish','closed','closed','','organization-for-international-cooperation','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1462,30,'2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00',