st be fluent in both written Chinese and English \n<br />• Organized and detail oriented \n<br />• Able to make sound judgment, effective problem solving skills. \n<br />• Positive working attitude \n<br /> \n<br />','Public Health Graduate Intern','','publish','closed','closed','','public-health-graduate-intern','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1502',0,'noo_job','',0),(1503,30,'2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Overview of Company: \n<br />Brain Power Wellness (\n<a href=\"http://www.brainpowerwellness.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.brainpowerwellness.com</a>) is an innovative social emotional program that introduces a whole child whole brain approach to learning. The Brain Education curriculum has been implemented in over 400 schools and we have trained 15,000 teachers and 250,000 students in Pre-Schools, Elementary and Middle Schools primarily in the New York area. “Brain Breaks” are introduced throughout the day to enhance the Brain Power 10 components: team building, physical health, focus, mindfulness, memory, emotional wellness, confidence, creativity, character and citizenship. The program is based on neuroscience with the goal of maximizing the full potential of the human brain and creating citizens in our communities who are healthy, happy, peaceful and productive members in our society. Join a movement that is dedicated to creating positive change in our educational system. During the year our instructors provide trainings in the schools. Over the Summer, our talented team certifies instructors from across the U.S. and conducts family and children\'s programs in New York City and Upstate New York. \n<br /> \n<br />Overview of Position: \n<br />The goal of the Summer internship is to train, certify and provide hands-on experience teaching Brain Education activities so that we can hire and expand our team of instructors when schools resume in September 2018. Interns will have the unique opportunity to receive certification in Brain Education at no cost to them (value: $6,800); receive hands on teaching experience and learn various skills related to implementing programs by directly supporting the Brain Power Wellness team. Interns will directly experience the personal benefits of the program and learn: how to teach 50 physical, emotional/social and cognitive exercises to children and adults; the fundamentals of positive discipline; and be able to speak to the benefits and merits of Brain Education. In addition, interns will assist our trainers who are certifying instructors to teach children, adults, seniors and individuals with special needs, as well as implement various Summer Brain Education programs with children and families. Upon successful completion of the internship and an excellent evaluation, Summer Interns will qualify for an interview for a full or part time position as a Brain Power Wellness Instructor starting in the Fall of 2018. Internship hours will be paid an hourly rate of $12 per hour. Hours related to certification and training are unpaid. Interns receive free certification training (valued at $6,800) in addition to free accommodation and meals. As this is a small company, interns will have the opportunity to learn about various aspects of the company and make a significant contribution during the internship. \n<br />SUBMIT APPLICATIONS/ENQUIRIES TO: katie@brainpowerwellness.com for a personal response ! \n<br /> \n<br />Check out the videos on our website to see the impact you will have in schools \n<a href=\"http://www.brainpowerwellness.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.brainpowerwellness.com</a> \n<br /><h3>Responsibilities</h3> Include but are not limited to: \n<br />HOURS: Summer internship begins July 9th and ends August 31st 2018. Flexibility is required with dates/times according to program schedule. Minimum 24 hrs/week - additional hours available. Dates 