osting social media content to promote trainings &amp; update website \n<br />:Other related tasks as assigned by Brain Power Wellness Team \n<br />NOTE: For non training hours intern will be paid<h2>Requirements</h2> The ideal candidates will: \n<br /> \n<br />1. Be studying or have a career interest in: Education, Psychology, Health &amp; Wellness, Social Emotional Wellness, Health &amp; Wellness, Yoga, Mindfulness, Sociology, Mental Health, Humanities, Social/Human Services. 2. Be dedicated to the mission and philosophy of the company which gives practical tools to program participants to their improve physical, emotional/social and cognitive health. 3. Demonstrate a commitment to improving their own personal health and wellness and making self care a priority in their lives. 4. Have a genuine interest in a career that is creating a positive impact in the world and one that will challenge them personally and support their personal growth. 5. Have strong interpersonal skills, be self starters who are positive, self-motivated, enthusiastic and demonstrate a commitment to completing tasks, and initiate seeking clarification and support. 6. Be excellent team players; able to adapt quickly to assignment changes; receptive to and embrace constructive criticism; and implement feedback into their work style. 7. Be able to adapt to a fast-paced environment, manage their stress well, be very flexible and adaptable to changes and requests. 8. Have excellent English verbal and written communication skills and ability to communicate with people at all levels of the company. 9. Have proficiency in Microsoft Office. \n<br /> \n<br />','Brain Power Instructor Intern (with the potential to be hired in Sept. 2018)','','publish','closed','closed','','brain-power-instructor-intern-with-the-potential-to-be-hired-in-sept-2018','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1503',0,'noo_job','',0),(1504,30,'1970-01-01 08:00: