 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1513',0,'noo_job','',0),(1514,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Meyer Vacation Rentals','Meyer Vacation Rentals','','publish','closed','closed','','meyer-vacation-rentals','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1515,30,'2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Shop &amp; Support turns everyday purchases into charitable donations that supports causes. We partner with merchants and charities to make an impact. Do good while shopping! \n<br /> \n<br />At Shop &amp; Support, we are always on the lookout for new energy and support for our work. Interns play a key role in helping us further what we do as an organization and in expanding our ability to fulfill our mission: Funding nonprofits through consumer purchases. \n<br /> \n<br />We love our interns. Each new team means a new group experiencing Shop &amp; Support in a deep and unique way, bringing its history and experience to the position while learning a host of new perspectives and skills. Our goals for interns are threefold: that they grow as individuals, professionally and personally; that they help us achieve more than we otherwise could; and that they become deeper advocates of the work that we do and the individuals we partner with around the globe. The internship is not lacking in fun, but it’s also a lot of work. Ultimately, it’s about a cause bigger than all of us, as we strive to see change in others’ lives. \n<br /> \n<br />We are a group of passionate people doing what we love in order to show love to others around the world. We are often blown away by the opportunity we have to play a part in making this world better. As an organization, we are working to show that doing business and doing good can mean more, connect more, and impact more, than ever before. We are about creatively challenging outdated methods, and about finding and proving new ways to empower individuals and communities around the world. Because we know that with every life impacted, the ripples continue far beyond the immediately seen. \n<br /> \n<br />This internship will be demanding, but it will be ever more rewarding. It will mean working with strangers who will become close friends, working long hours in new surroundings, learning the ins-and-outs of the nonprofit world and social enterprise, pouring your heart and soul into projects you deeply believe in, and tirelessly spreading the message that with people’s purchases, lives are changed. Oh, and it’s really fun, too. And at the heart of it all will be the stories of the people, the families, and the communities that are strengthened daily by the work that we do. \n<br /> \n<br />Together, we will change the world. \n<br /><h3>Responsibilities</h3> - Work with development team to research potential leads \n<br />- Integrate/analyze data workflow using Salesforce \n<br />- Help develop pitch decks \n<br />- Contribute on business development pitches (as needed) \n<br />- Offer thought out outside-of-the-box thinking for current and future projects \n<br /> \n<br />Internship Details \n<br />- U.S Work Authorization is NOT required \n<br />- Internship length and start date will be discussed upon interview \n<br />- Internship applicants must be at least 18 years of age. \n<br />- Internships are unpaid. \n<br />- Internships are available in part time (15-20 hrs/week) or more, we are flexible. \n<br />- Work option include on-site \n<br />- Mac access is required \n<br /> \n<br />College credit is available and recommended for the internship. We suggest that you start talking with your school advisor now about the steps necessary for this. We are more than willing to fill out the needed paperwork to ensure that you get academic credit for your work with us. \n<br /> \n<br />NOTE: Shop &amp; Support internships are designed for undergraduate students or recently graduated individuals. Although there is not a strict age requirement other than minimum of 18, college-aged individuals tend to get the most out of our internship experience.<h2>Requirements</h2> - The ideal candidate will be in Orange County \n<br />- The ideal candidate will be pursuing a career in business with experience in sales and marketing. \n<br />- Work well in a team setting and communicate well with others \n<br />- Experience with Salesforce or equivalent CRM is helpful. \n<br />- Intern must be comfortable making phone calls to obtain information. \n<br />- Attention to detail and a working knowledge of how to use spreadsheets (Excel/Google Sheets) is a must. \n<br />- Proficiency on the Mac OS and experience with Google Apps products (Google Drive, Google Calendar, etc.) is a must. \n<br /> \n<br />Application Guidelines \n<br />Internship Application Checklist- Business Development \n<br /> \n<br />Please include the following for your application to be reviewed: \n<br />- Resume highlighting your education/work/volunteer experience \n<br />- Cover letter explaining what attracts you to Shop &amp; Support and why you’re a perfect fit \n<br />- Answer 3 YOU ARE WHO? Questions \n<br /> \n<br />Please submit your application via e-mail at this address: caredesk@shopandsupport.org \n<br /> \n<br />YOU ARE WHO? \n<br />We want - we need - to know who you are! What do you like, what do you dream about, what drives you crazy? We want to get to know your personality, your style and see what you\'re about. Be honest. Be yourself. Please choose 3 of the following questions to answer in writing. Keep writing to half page or less per questions. We\'re looking for you to tell us the answer to the question in a casual way - think of it as a chance to send us a glimpse of an interview with you. \n<br /> \n<br />1. Why are you interested in social enterprise? \n<br />2. Is business the best avenue for social change? \n<br />3. What is the best book you’ve read in the last year? Why? \n<br />4. Tell us about one moment that changed the course of your life. \n<br />5. What is one thing in the world that makes you angry? \n<br />6. Who or what have you most loved and why? \n<br />7. Tell us about 3 websites that you frequent most. \n<br />8. What is the biggest need in our current world? \n<br />9. Tell us about the sweetest place you’ve ever travelled to. \n<br />10. What is one question you would ask us?','Business Development - Marketing Internship','','publish','closed','closed','','business-development-marketing-internship','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1515',0,'noo_job','',0),(1516,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Shop & Support','Shop & Support','','publish','closed','closed','','shopsupport','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1517,30,'2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> ElectroCell Systems is a Manufacturer of a state of the art Water Enhancement Equipment designed to improve the overall effiecncy and effectiveness of Chillers/Cooling Towers and Boilers for Commercial , Industrial and Institutional Facilities. \n<br /> \n<br />We need an intern to help develop and manage our Marketing, Sales and Advertising Information - including Graphics, Email Contacts, CRM, and communications with Customers and Sales Organization.<h3>Responsibilities</h3> Interact with enteral and outside Sales and Marketing Team, including Prospective Customers<h2>Requirements</h2> Proficient knowledge of Mircosoft Suite of Products, Graphics, Trade Show Constant Contact, CRM, Website Management and Revisions.','Administrative Coordinator','','publish','closed','closed','','administrative-coordinator','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1517',0,'noo_job','',0),(1518,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Electro