th flexibility allowed for the selected candidate\'s school schedule and last through the summer with the potential of a longer period depending on workload need. The duration of the internship and work schedule will be discussed when a job offer is made. \n<br /><h3>Responsibilities</h3> As an intern, you will have the opportunity to assist in the preparation of the Biennial Energy Report (BER) and become an integral member of our team. The BER is a statutorily required report that provides a comprehensive overview of energy resources, policies, trends and forecasts in Oregon. The report includes timely information that provides a foundation for decision-making about energy issues. The report covers all fuels and energy resources, looks across utility territories, and evaluates the Oregon impacts from regional and national planning. In addition to a summary and synthesis of Oregon\'s energy data, each issue of the report includes information and analysis of relevant topics selected in consultation with energy suppliers and stakeholders. The report is submitted to the Legislature in advance of each odd-numbered year legislative session, ensuring that legislators have ready access to energy information they may need during the session. \n<br /> \n<br /><h2>Requirements</h2> Minimum Requirements \n<br />•Be a student in an accredited degree program who has completed at least your freshman year in an Associate or Bachelor\'s degree program. OR \n<br />•Be a student enrolled in graduate school. \n<br />Requested Skills •Data analysis and/or data modeling. \n<br />•Attention to detail. \n<br />•Academic research. \n<br />•Work well as a team member. \n<br /> \n<br />For more information and to apply online, please visit \n<a href=\"http://www.tinyurl.com/WorkAtODOE\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.tinyurl.com/WorkAtODOE</a> \n<br /> \n<br />Applications must be received by 11:59 pm on April 16, 2018.','BER Data Analyst Intern','','publish','closed','closed','','ber-data-analyst-intern','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1546',0,'noo_job','',0),(1547,30,'2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Los Angeles-area museums and visual arts organizations are currently seeking eligible interns for the summer of 2018. Eligibility for the internships is limited to currently enrolled undergraduates who reside in or attend college in Los Angeles County. Students must have completed at least one semester of college by June 2018, and those who will complete their degree by September 1, 2018 are also eligible to apply. Candidates are sought from all areas of undergraduate study and are not required to have demonstrated a previous commitment to the visual arts. The internships are intended for outstanding students who are members of groups underrepresented in museums and visual arts organizations, including but not limited to: individuals of African American, Asian, Latino/Hispanic, Native American, and Pacific Islander descent. \n<br /> \n<br />Compensation: $5500 stipend \n<br /> \n<br />How Candidates Apply \n<br /> \n<br />Please visit this website for a list of participating organizations: \n<a href=\"http://www.getty.edu/foundation/initiatives/current/mui/internship_positions.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.getty.edu/foundation/initiatives/current/mui/internship_positions.html</a> \n<br /> \n<br />Eligible undergraduates should review the list of opportunities at the linked website and contact the participating organizations directly for information about the available internship positions and application procedures.nullnull','2018 Multicultural Undergraduate Internships in Los Angeles','','publish','closed','closed','','2018-multicultural-undergraduate-internships-in-los-angeles','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1547',0,'noo_job','',0),(1548