s. The Court has an onsite caf&eacute; and a free gym available to all employees. For more information on the Court of Appeals, please visit \n<a href=\"http://www.ca9.uscourts.gov/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.ca9.uscourts.gov</a>.null<h2>Requirements</h2> The internship runs from June 18 - August 31 (depending on workload and schedule). We’re looking for someone who is flexible, outgoing, able to work well in a team environment, very comfortable with Windows operating systems, and able to pick up new applications quickly. Accuracy and timeliness are especially important in this role, since we have multiple deadlines to meet each week in order to get employees on and off payroll and set up their benefits. \n<br /> \n<br />Please submit a resume and cover letter describing how you meet the qualifications to our career portal: \n<a href=\"https://ca9-employment.breezy.hr/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://ca9-employment.breezy.hr/</a>','Human Resources Intern','','publish','closed','closed','','human-resources-intern','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1569',0,'noo_job','',0),(1570,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','U.S. Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit','U.S. Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit','','publish','closed','closed','','us-court-of-appeals-ninth-circuit','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1571,30,'2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> OVERVIEW \n<br />The Maryland Association of Nonprofit Organizations (Maryland Nonprofits) is one of the largest and most successful state associations of nonprofits with over 1,200 organizational members, 150 associate members, and 16 staff to serve them. Our mission is to strengthen, educate and engage nonprofits so they can successfully achieve their missions. \n<br /> \n<br />Maryland Nonprofits is the primary resources for advice and assistance on nonprofit management issues for the state’s nonprofit community. We conduct training programs and provide technical assistance in most areas of nonprofit management subjects; promote opportunities for information sharing and networking and represent the interests of our members and the nonprofit sector before the General Assembly, Congress, and local governments. We are recognized across the nonprofit sector and among policymakers, the media, opinion leaders, and the general public, as the leading representative of and the authoritative source of information about the state’s nonprofit sector. \n<br /> \n<br />POSITION DESCRIPTION \n<br />Maryland Nonprofits seeks a volunteer Marketing and Communications Intern. Applicant should have considerable skills in marketing, communications, website management, blogging, social media, as well as a strong interest in working within the nonprofit sector. This is an unpaid internship. \n<br /> \n<br />DURATION \n<br />A flexible part-time schedule is available for this volunteer internship position. Intern should expect to work 16-24 hours per week between May - August, 2018 (start and end dates are flexible). \n<br /> \n<br />BENEFITS OF THIS INTERNSHIP \n<br />The intern will gain project management experience, as well as strengthening their core knowledge of online marketing and strategy. The intern will also gain a comprehensive understanding of data analytics and identifying trends across multiple platforms. Finally, intern will leave the experience with a portfolio of quantitative accomplishments specific to online marketing and website management. \n<br /> \n<br />This opportunity is unpaid. Dates and times are flexible. \n<br /> \n<br />IMPORTANT: To be considered for this internship, please submit the items listed below to Lydia Alcock at lalcock@mdnonprofit.org. Please include your name and &quot;Marketing and Communications Internship&quot; in the email subject line. \n<br /> \n<br />1. Your resume (Submit as a PDF) \n<br />2. A customized cover letter explaining: your interest in Maryland Nonprofits, the nonprofit sector, and the Marketing and Communications Intern position; how your skills and past experiences prepare you for the role; and what you hope to get out of an internship. This will be considered as a sample of your writing ability. (Submit as a PDF) \n<br />3. Two writing samples in addition to your cover letter. (Submit as a PDF)<h3>Responsibilities</h3> Intern will participate in a structured program with responsibilities that will include: \n<br />1. Helping execute social media marketing campaigns from initial planning stages through to final reporting \n<br />2. Assisting with day-to-day social media management, including but not limited to scheduling posts and \n<br />community management. \n<br />3. Assisting with the design/production of content for social media, including images, copy, etc. \n<br />4. Helping create the Weekly Member Update email \n<br />5. Staying current with best practices related to PR and social media, and making recommendations for new and improved strategies \n<br />6. Researching and curating lists of influencers, hashtags, etc \n<br />7. Helping with redesigning the Maryland Nonprofits website \n<br />8. Assistance with Maryland Nonprofits\' Annual Conference in October 2018 \n<br /> \n<br />This opportunity is unpaid. Dates and times are flexible. \n<br /> \n<br />IMPORTANT: To be considered for this internship, please submit the items listed below to Lydia Alcock at lalcock@mdnonprofit.org. Please include your name and &quot;Marketing and Communications Internship&quot; in the email subject line. \n<br /> \n<br />1. Your resume (Submit as a PDF) \n<br />2. A customized cover letter explaining: your interest in Maryland Nonprofits, the nonprofit sector, and the Marketing and Communications Intern position; how your skills and past experiences prepare you for the role; and what you hope to get out of an internship. This will be considered as a sample of your writing ability. (Submit as a PDF) \n<br />3. Two writing samples in addition to your cover letter. (Submit as a PDF)<h2>Requirements</h2> Candidates should be working towards an undergraduate or graduate degree in fields such as marketing, communications, nonprofit management, or majors related to marketing and digital media. Strong writing and editing abilities required. Skills in graphic design, research, Google Analytics, and website management a plus. Candidates should be quick to learn new technology tools such as HootSuite, Box.com, MailChimp, WordPress, Trello, Salesforce, etc. \n<br /> \n<br />This opportunity is unpaid. Dates and times are flexible. Applicants should be prepared to work at least 16 hours a week from June - August 2018.','Maryland Nonprofits Marketing and Communications Intern (unpaid)','','publish','closed','closed','','maryland-nonprofits-marketing-and-communications-intern-unpaid','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1571',0,'noo_job','',0),(1572,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Maryland Nonprofits','Maryland Nonprofits','','publish','closed','closed','','maryland-nonprofits','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1573,30,'2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> We are a multifaceted law firm with a focus on business, entertainment and sports. We assess the business needs of our clients and provide sound strategies that will enable them to grow their business and enhance their brands. We provide a wide spectrum of services ranging from legal counsel, private equity deals to brand management. \n<br /> \n<br />Through this position, our intern will learn the structure of a start up firm. The intern will work with attorneys, emerging companies and an assortment of clients. The intern will be exposed to entrepreneurial businesses nationwide, social media and brand management trends and the research and development of projects. \n<br /> \n<br />As an intern with us you will: \n<br /> \n<br />- Gain exposure and familiarity to a broad spectrum of businesses and industries \n<br /> \n<br />- Improve your research and computer skills, interpersonal skills, and general business analysis ability \n<br /> \n<br />- Become more marketable to potential employers by having a substantive role on resume \n<br /> \n<br />-Become familiar with branding and marketing in the business, entertainment and sports industry. \n<br /><h3>Responsibilities</h3> The Intern will work closely with the Partner of the Firm and: \n<br />-Conduct Legal Research on cases \n<br />-Attend Client meetings and take meticulous notes \n<br />-Follow up with new clients regarding the Firm\'s services \n<br />-Send out Invoices to clients<h2>Requirements</h2> The intern must be: \n<br />Reliable, \n<br />Computer proficient \n<br />Must be detail-oriented \n<br />Have impeccable follow-up skills \n<br />Feel comfortable working independently and \n<br />Have a clear telephone speaking voice.','Legal Research Assistant','','publish','closed','closed','','legal-research-assistant','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1573',0,'noo_job','',0),(1574,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Jacques Law Firm','Jacques Law Firm','','publish','closed','closed','','jacques-law-firm','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1575,30,'2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> The Buzzell Company is a highly respected, fast-paced public relations and marketing firm located in the Design District. We have a wide range of clients in the arts, hospitality, professional services, retail, real estate and legal industries.<h3>Responsibilities</h3> JOB DESCRIPTION \n<br />Duties include, but are not limited to: \n<br />• Reading assigned publi