ativity, flexibility, and variety \n<br />- Exhibits personal qualities, such as open-mindedness, enthusiasm, and adaptability \n<br />- Prefers challenges, fast pace, new ideas, future focus, and unstructured environment','Social Media & Community Management Intern','','publish','closed','closed','','social-mediacommunity-management-intern','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1579',0,'noo_job','',0),(1580,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Call Your Admin','Call Your Admin','','publish','closed','closed','','call-your-admin','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1581,30,'2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Join Construction managers on job sites to review unit layouts and take room and utility measurements at locations; assist in procuring all material items from various vendors, place/track firm orders and quantities, coordinate scheduling, material deliveries: research alternative material sources, options &amp; pricing. \n<br /> \n<br />Stipend for commute and lunch up to $15/day.<h3>Responsibilities</h3> Commitment: 4 days/week not including Fridays<h2>Requirements</h2> Senior in College or a Graduate School Student','Construction Manager\'s Assistant','','publish','closed','closed','','construction-managers-assistant','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1581',0,'noo_job','',0),(1582,30,'2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Philly Views is looking for a tech-savvy, social media-obsessed Marketing and Social Media Intern to help promote our growing online publication. Launched in 2017, Philly Views has already captured a wide and varied audience, and we’re constantly searching for new ways to improve our coverage and expand readership. \n<br /> \n<br />What the Marketing Internship is like: \n<br />Our marketing internship includes opportunities to work on brand strategy, outreach, social media, and more. You will have an integral role in helping Philly Views reach a wider audience. This includes helping to conceive and execute promotion strategy through direct outreach as well as through social media curation. We are looking for someone familiar with Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, Reddit, and other social media platforms. \n<br /> \n<br />What we can offer you: \n<br />Freedom to try your ideas. Remember, you’ll be working on something that is building, rather than already built. We’re not stuck in our ways. \n<br />A flexible schedule that adapts to your class structure or other responsibilities. \n<br />College and university credits. Our intern program is adaptable to most credit requirements. \n<br />The opportunity to work alongside professional digital marketers to gain perspective and guidance. \n<br />This is an unpaid opportunity based at our office at 10th and Spring Garden. Those interested in applying for the marketing internship can send a resume, any past work samples, and a short cover letter introducing yourself to Matt Schickling at editor@phillyviews.com.<h3>Responsibilities</h3> This is a self-defined role, in a way. There will be direction but your general responsibility is to help grow our brand. \n<br />We\'re really looking for someone obsessed with social media and marketing and wants to take ownership of this role.<h2>Requirements</h2> Who we’re looking for: \n<br />Creative individuals with an eye for what makes Philadelphia and its citizens unique. \n<br />Motivated thinkers with fresh ideas and the drive to innovate. \n<br />Recent graduates or current student studying marketing, communications, digital media, or related field. You do not have to be in pursuit of a degree, though.','Philly Views Marketing and Social Media Summer Internship','','publish','closed','closed','','philly-views-marketing-and-social-media-summer-internship','','','2