ices of an international staffing agency. The agencies we use are CIEE Camp Exchange USA, Camp Leaders and 3 Adventures. \n<br /> \n<br />','Multi Media Editor at Children\'s Summer Camp','','publish','closed','closed','','multi-media-editor-at-childrens-summer-camp','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1584',0,'noo_job','',0),(1585,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Kingsley Pines','Kingsley Pines','','publish','closed','closed','','kingsley-pines','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1586,30,'2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> The American Institute of Physics is seeking an enthusiastic intern who is passionate about learning about critical business-related functions within Human Resources. \n<br /> \n<br />Essential Functions: \n<br /> \n<br />This is an onsite position and can be 30-40 hours/week during the summer with possible continuation at 10 hours/week during the school year. Assignments will be project based and will support the HR department primarily in the areas of talent management, training &amp; development, and process documentation. Completed projects from internship will be used by the organization for months and years into the future. This position will be a full member of the HR team, supporting office coverage and assisting with additional projects as needs arise.<h3>Responsibilities</h3> Tasks include, but are not limited to: \n<br /> \n<br />1) Document HR processes by observing and interviewing HR team \n<br />2) Curate LinkedIn Learning video playlists on topics in management, coaching and Office 365 \n<br />3) Write staff communications reminders to support Performance Management program<h2>Requirements</h2> Qualifications: \n<br /> \n<br />• Undergraduate or graduate student. Preferred majors in HR, Management, Communications or Psychology \n<br />• Must maintain a 3.0 or higher GPA