e and outside of the department \n<br />- Design IT systems and networks ensuring the right architecture and functionality \n<br />- Support new technology implementation \n<br />- Train the STW volunteers in new and existing IT systems \n<br />- Provide assistance with technical issues \n<br />- Revise existing systems and suggest improvements \n<br />- Manage all aspects of the web hosting infrastructure, software, Web Application Firewall and Forum collaboration, SEO, and Web-related SQL Server databases \n<br /> \n<br /> \n<br />Your Take Away….. \n<br />- Chance to develop or master your professional skills \n<br />- Advance &amp; improve your project management skills \n<br />- Work with a team of diverse professionals from all over the world \n<br />- Opportunity to handle multiple projects \n<br />- Be a part of a mission to save our resources and make a deep impact \n<br /><h2>Requirements</h2> Apply Now if you have…. \n<br />- Ability to troubleshoot hardware, software and network problems \n<br />- Experience with various operating systems and databases \n<br />- Experience in project management \n<br />- An analytical mind with problem-solving abilities \n<br />- A team player with excellent communication and presentation skills \n<br />- Customer service orientation \n<br />- BSc/BA in computer science, IT or relevant field; MSc/MBA in business will be a plus \n<br />- Professional certification (e.g. CompTIA A+) is an asset \n<br /> \n<br />How to apply: \n<br /> \n<br /> \n<br /> \n<br />If interested, please submit your resume to newvolunteers@savethewater.org We would love to hear from you! \n<br /> \n<br />&copy; 2018','TECHNOLOGY CONSULTANT: IT MANAGEMENT PLAN (REMOTE)','','publish','closed','closed','','technology-consultant-it-management-plan-remote','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1609',0,'noo_job','',0),(1610,30,'2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> About the NYC City Council and Councilmember Keith Powers \n<br />Council Member Keith Powers is chair of the New York City Council’s Criminal Justice Committee, providing oversight to the NYC Department of Corrections and the Department of Probation and overseeing the closure of Rikers Island. He represents the 4th Council District in Manhattan, covering the Upper East Side, Carnegie Hill, Midtown, Murray Hill, Turtle Bay, Sutton Place, Tudor City and Stuyvesant Town and Peter Cooper Village. Council Member Powers is a lifelong New Yorker and a third generation resident the district. \n<br /> \n<br />Press and Communications Fellow Position Outline \n<br />Are you interested in making our city a better place to live, using communications to drive a key message to constituents? The office of City Council Member Keith Powers is searching for a self-motivated, high-energy and organized undergraduate or graduate student who has a passion for public service and media. \n<br /> \n<br /><h3>Responsibilities</h3> • Collaborate with Communications director to draft editorial content and organize press lists \n<br />• Support office’s editorial strategy and craft a range of communications on a moment’s notice \n<br />• Identify external opportunities for the Council Member to participate in or be featured in a news moment \n<br />• Analyze results and identify opportunities to optimize future communications \n<br /> \n<br />To apply please send resume and cover letter to kpowers@council.nyc.gov with the subject line: Press and Communications Fellow \n<br /><h2>Requirements</h2> Key qualifications: \n<br />• Excellent writing and editing skills \n<br />• Strong ability to write and edit copy in a fast-paced and deadline-driven environment, managing the important details along the way, for email communications and newsletter \n<br />• Understanding of New York media landscape and best practices, with an emphasis on press opportunities \n<br />• An innovative and entrepreneurial spirit and excitement \n<br />• Strong interest in communications, government, and public policy \n<br />• A good sense of humor \n<br />• Solutions-oriented \n<br /> \n<br />Preferences \n<br />- Journalism graduate students \n<br />- Concentration in public relations \n<br /> \n<br /> \n<br />','New York City Council Communications Internship','','publish','closed','closed','','new-york-city-council-communications-internship','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1610',0,'noo_job','',0),(1611,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','New York City Council','New York City Council','','publish','closed','closed','','new-york-city-council','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1612,30,'2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> We are the largest and smartest marketplace for sports sponsorship. \n<br />We are looking for an intern to maintain and further develop our social media channels as well as come up with new ways of marketing e.g. events, blogs, PR, podcasts etc. \n<br /> \n<br />We are looking for someone interested in sports, creative and who can work independently as well as in a team.<h3>Responsibilities</h3> You will be working with all social media platforms, writing articles, reading sports articles to pick out interesting information.<h2>Requirements</h2> You must be interested in sport, enjoy and use social media, have strong written english.','Social Media Marketing','','publish','closed','closed','','social-media-marketing','','','2018-04-06 00:00:00','2018-04-06 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1612',0,'noo_job','',0),(1613,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','OpenSponsorship','OpenSponsorship','','publish','closed','closed','','opensponsorship','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1614,30,'2018-04-06 00:00: