INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1634,30,'2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Our trail rides are truly unique. We’re not a nose-to-tail outfit. Our horses enjoy their jobs and perform them impeccably. Each ride is a private ride, custom tailored to your riding ability. If you’re a beginning or fearful rider, we have horses that will teach you and keep you safe through a willing partnership. If you’re a more advanced rider, you’ll love the freedom of trotting and loping on a kind-minded, sure-footed horse who will listen to your every cue.<h3>Responsibilities</h3> As a summer intern you will be involved in the following… \n<br />•Cleaning paddocks and corrals, filling/cleaning water troughs and other barn chores \n<br />•Feeding/graining horses \n<br />•Grooming, doctoring, assisting the farrier with horses \n<br />•Tacking and guiding/dragging trail rides (dragging is riding in the rear of the ride) \n<br />•Exercising and training horses \n<br />•Maintaining/repairing tack \n<br />•Accompanying staff members on various errands, including to the trainer we use to start our young horses, horse buying trips, and education expositions. \n<br /> \n<br />We will provide you with the following… \n<br />•Room (your own bedroom with connecting bathroom/shower) \n<br />•Board (three meals a day) \n<br />•A vehicle to drive (2001 F-150 truck, safety inspected with new tires) \n<br />•Fuel for work related driving (any driving you do outside KB HORSES business is at your expense) \n<br />•Shared/Individual tips received from clients for rides/events you’ve worked \n<br />•A saddle and horse to ride during your internship \n<br />•Instruction and coaching as needed to accomplish your duties \n<br />•Full tuition paid for horsemanship-101 course and accompanying book<h2>Requirements</h2> Must be 18 or older. \n<br />Intermediate to advanced riders only.','Wrangler/Barn Hand','','publish','closed','closed','','wranglerbarn-hand','','','2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1634',0,'noo_job','',0),(1635,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','KB HORSES','KB HORSES','','publish','closed','closed','','kb-horses','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1636,30,'2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Kinema Fitness is a full service fitness center management and wellness company. We currently work with some of the most premier brands in the country managing their on site fitness centers. We are currently looking for one intern that is local to Chicago to assist us with a brand new gym in downtown Chicago. \n<br /> \n<br />This intern will be involved in all facets of operating a fitness center including programming, sales, marketing and branding, admin, event planning, outreach while working directly with our general manager and fitness director.<h3>Responsibilities</h3> Day to day operations will include greeting and engaging members, assisting in creating reports, working directly in our management system, working directly with our graphic designers, creating new wellness programs<h2>Requirements</h2> Studying in a health related degree with a passion for wellness \n<br />Experience working with Google Drive/Dropbox \n<br />Experience with Microsoft Office \n<br />','Corporate Wellness Intern for Brand New Corporate Gym','','publish','closed','closed','','corporate-wellness-intern-for-brand-new-corporate-gym','','','2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1636',0,'noo_job','',0),(1637,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Kinema Fitness','Kinema Fitness','','publish','closed','closed','','kinema-fitness','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1638,30,'2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> The Scranton Fringe Festival is a performing arts festival dedicated to creating a bold and engaging platform for creative and thought provoking art with minimal risk to artist and audience. We are a small yet devoted non-profit based organization which greatly depends upon the assistance of volunteers and creative-minded supporters. \n<br /> \n<br />Interns will assist in strengthening Scranton Fringe’s connections with our diverse community partners, which include local and national performing artists, avid theater goers, sponsors and donors, and the public at large. We desire applicants who are equipped to effectively establish meaningful connections to both artisans and the local arts community through various social media platforms (Twitter, Facebook, Instagram, Snapchat, and blogging). Interns will also help plan and implement a variety of outreach events, working closely with the Executive Director and Managing Director to promote awareness of the festival. Applicants must showcase a thorough understanding of the principles of marketing, promotion, and time management. This internship will build to the 2018 Scranton Fringe (September 22nd - 30th). \n<br /><h3>Responsibilities</h3> All interns will assist in the development and execution of short and long term event planning, including the actual festival as well as fundraisers, community outreach, volunteer and artist information sessions. \n<br />Interns will be expected to help maintain social media marketing, including but not limited to creating/managing Facebook, Twitter and blog content. \n<br /> \n<br />Interns will work with directors to assist with the specific needs of projects as they develop, and attend weekly board meetings to stay up to date and give reports. Interns will be expected to attend Scranton Fringe events on nights and weekends, with advanced notice of the type of event and duties required. Interns will need to attend Scranton Fringe throughout the entire event week (September 22nd - 30th), providing behind the scenes support and documenting various events as needed. \n<br /><h2>Requirements</h2> All college students / majors are welcome to submit. However, we do appreciate students who have majored or completed courses within the Arts Administration, Fine Arts, Communications and Marketing areas. Those with graphic design skills, experience managing social media platforms, and practical knowledge of promotions principles are encouraged to apply as well. We seek skilled communicators who are able to create meaningful connections within the artistic community. \n<br /> \n<br />This position has the capability to develop around the applicants own interests and strengths. The focus can be on marketing/PR/social media, arts administration, sponsor/artist/community outreach, graphic design, writing, financial management, or any number of other areas of importance for a festival of this size (approx 300 artists/6000 audience and growing). \n<br /> \n<br />We seek creative, free thinking minds who are also able to work together as a productive team. A dedicated, optimistic, creative, and expressive soul is exactly what the Scranton Fringe is searching for. All interns will take direction from the directors as well as select members of the board for project-specific goals. \n<br /> \n<br />PLEASE NOTE: . Interns will be required to attend monthly board meetings as well as various events scheduled on nights/weekends. The schedule will be set in advance. Applicants who live outside of the greater Scranton area during the summer cannot be considered for logistical reasons. \n<br />','Scranton Fringe Festival Social Media & Marketing Internship','','publish','closed','closed','','scranton-fringe-festival-social-mediamarketing-internship','','','2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1638',0,'noo_job','',0),(1639,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Scranton Fringe','Scranton Fringe','','publish','closed','closed','','scranton-fringe',''