, with advanced notice of the type of event and duties required. Interns will need to attend Scranton Fringe throughout the entire event week (September 22nd - 30th), providing behind the scenes support and documenting various events as needed. \n<br /><h2>Requirements</h2> All college students / majors are welcome to submit. However, we do appreciate students who have majored or completed courses within the Arts Administration, Fine Arts, Communications, and Marketing areas. Those with graphic design skills, experience managing social media platforms, and practical knowledge of promotions principles are encouraged to apply as well. We seek skilled communicators who are able to create meaningful connections within the artistic community. \n<br /> \n<br />This position has the capability to develop around the applicants own interests and strengths. The focus can be on marketing/PR/social media, arts administration, sponsor/artist/community outreach, graphic design, writing, financial management, or any number of other areas of importance for a festival of this size (approx 300 artists/6000 audience and growing). \n<br /> \n<br />We seek creative, free thinking minds who are also able to work together as a productive team. A dedicated, optimistic, creative, and expressive soul is exactly what the Scranton Fringe is searching for to fill this position. All interns will take direction from the directors as well as select members of the board for project-specific goals. \n<br /> \n<br />PLEASE NOTE: Interns will be required to attend monthly board meetings as well as various events scheduled on nights/weekends. The schedule will be set in advance and include the summer through the end of September.','Scranton Fringe Festival Arts Administration Internship','','publish','closed','closed','','scranton-fringe-festival-arts-administration-internship','','','2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1640',0,'noo_job','',0),(1641,30,'2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> We are looking for a part-time assistant to provide administrative support to a growing real estate office that specializes in working with investors. We provide brokerage, property management and consulting services. The candidate will get exposed to marketing, sales, and operations tasks associated with running a small business in real estate. This is a good opportunity for those with an interest in real estate investing or those seeking to work as a real estate agent. We are located near City Hall in Chester and work with clients across Delaware County and West Philadelphia. \n<br /><h3>Responsibilities</h3> (50%) Perform general admin tasks \n<br />• Organize client and property files in online and offline directory \n<br />• Make follow up calls to confirm appointments with clients and contractors \n<br />• Enter data into property management system and customer database \n<br />• Run miscellaneous errands to support property management or sales \n<br />• Scan checks, contracts and receipts for filing \n<br /> \n<br />(30%) Marketing/Business Development Support \n<br />• Support general marketing and listing campaigns including creating landing pages, posting online ads, and tracking results \n<br />• Track results of marketing campaigns \n<br />• Curate and schedule social media posts \n<br />• Make website updates \n<br /> \n<br />(20%) Research \n<br />• Complete Internet research to support projects and social media \n<br />• Support mailing and phone campaigns by tracking down information online \n<br />• Track sales and rent information for target neighborhoods for market update reports<h2>Requirements</h2> Key skills \n<br />• Strong interpersonal skills \n<br />• Excellent phone and email communication skills \n<br />• Experience working in a small business \n<br />• Attention to detail \n<br />• Problem solving/math skills \n<br />• Can work independently \n<br />• Knowledge of Microsoft Excel, Word, Powerpoint, Publisher \n<br />• Some knowledge of Wordpress websites \n<br /> \n<br />A current driver\'s license is required. The intern must be able to work on-site. \n<br />','Real Estate Intern','','publish','closed','closed','','real-estate-intern','','','2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1641',0,'noo_job','',0),(1642,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Daniel Woods Real Estate Company','Daniel Woods Real Estate Company','','publish','closed','closed','','daniel-woods-real-estate-company','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1643,30,'2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Looking for someone who knows about neural networks and develop an algorithm for conservation projects for Kashmir World Foundation. \n<br /> \n<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.kashmirworldfoundation.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.kashmirworldfoundation.org</a><h3>Responsibilities</h3> Common fields of study include computer science, artificial intelligence, robotics and engineering. Artificial intelligence programmers should acquire training and experience with programming languages such as python, C, C++, etc and neural networks such as YOLO, Tensor flow, etc. Related studies in psychology and philosophy are also recommended.<h2>Requirements</h2> Artificial intelligence programmers have to perform calculations and need to have good mathematical skills to do so. They also need computer skills so that they can design and develop relevant software. Communication skills are important for artificial intelligence programmers because they must be able to clarify their objectives to others in their team, and they may be responsible for supervising other programmers as part of their duties. They might face unique challenges in their work so they also need to have good problem-solving skills.','Artificial Intelligence - Computer Science','','publish','closed','closed','','artificial-intelligence-computer-science','','','2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1643',0,'noo_job','',0),(1644,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Kashmir World Foundation','Kashmir World Foundation','','publish','closed','closed','','kashmir-world-foundation','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1645,30,'2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Looking for someone to write blog posts. \n<br /> \n<br />Please visit: \n<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.kashmirworldfoundation.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.kashmirworldfoundation.org</a><h3>Responsibilities</h3> - Assist with editorial projects and provide support to the Communications Editor. \n<br />- Proofreading both hard and electronic files, basic copyediting, and writing of proposals and reports; \n<br />- Assisting with or proofing of basic ads, flyers, brochures, invitations, etc. \n<br />- Work on special projects, as needed<h2>Requirements</h2> - Working towards a Bachelor’s degree in journalism, public relations, English, business communications, or communication arts. \n<br />- Strong organizational and communication skills with keen attention to detail and problem solving skills \n<br />- Knowledge of MS Office applications, especially Word, Excel, and PowerPoint \n<br />- Experience/interest in Web maintenance \n<br />- Familiarity with Adobe In Design and Adobe Acrobat is a plus','Editorial / Journalism Intern','','publish','closed','closed','','editorialjournalism-intern','','','2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1645',0,'noo_job','',0),(1646,30,'2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Looking for someone who is passionate about drones and wildlife conservation and counter poaching. \n<br /> \n<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.kashmirworldfoundation.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.kashmirworldfoundation.org</a><h3>Responsibilities</h3> Working in a team to build, test, modify, and operate drones. Also have an understanding of computer science for artificial intelligence.<h2>Requirements</h2> Can develop technologies from concept, specification through to implementation \n<br />Experience with static drones \n<br />Ability to provide drone solutions for specific requirements \n<br />Dynamic Engineers that have won drone related development competitions \n<br />Willing to learn and adapt new technologies','Drone Engineer','','publish','closed','closed','','drone-engineer','','','2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1646',0,'noo_job','',0),(1647,30,'2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Norse Interiors is the premier company in the U.S. offering Scandinavian-designed, artisanal components to retrofit IKEA furniture. We are changing the luxury furniture shopping experience by letting customers design bespoke pieces from sturdy, American-manufactured materials to fit over existing IKEA frames for storage cabinets and TV stands. The process is simple and sustainable, and the results are durable and elegant. \n<br /> \n<br />We\'re looking for a summer intern who can support all the daily activities connected to a start-up. \n<br /> \n<br /><h3>Responsibilities</h3> - Implement marketing strategy to align with business goals \n<br />- Generate, edit and publish compelling content to build social media following and daily web traffic \n<br />- Communicate with followers and customer queries in a timely manner \n<br />- Identify and have conversations with brand advocates and potential marketing partners \n<br />- Scale communities and connect with new people \n<br />- Monitor and analyze web traffic metrics \n<br />- Monitor and encourage customer reviews \n<br />- Research and stay up-to-date with competitors, marketing best practice, industry data and leaders \n<br />- Ad-hoc duties connected to a start-up<h2>Requirements</h2> You should major in marketing, communications, or similar business field. You need to be enthusiastic and self-starting to assist in all of our digital communications and marketing needs. You\'ll wear many hats and needs to be willing to take on any task, big or small. The ideal candidate is someone who is detail-oriented, creative, hard-working, and passionate about e-commerce and interior design.','Digital Communication and Marketing Intern','','publish','closed','closed','','digital-communication-and-marketing-intern','','','2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1647',0,'noo_job','',0),(1648,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Norse Interiors','Norse Interiors','','publish','closed','closed','','norse-interiors','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1649,30,'2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Please provide a sample of your work. We are a community organization focus on the issues of Equitable Justice daily living for everyone-- We address community issues of Housing , Crime &amp; Safety, Financial Wellness, Social Justice &amp; Protections for Our Elders based on solutions --- powerful graphics supporting our message allows us to reach a broader audience-- We welcome you to join our team of committed community positive game changers!<h3>Responsibilities</h3> - Assists in the design and development of layouts for marketing materials, using appealing graphics that are well organized \n<br />- Responsible to incorporate current design trends into each unique layout to produce an up-to-date style for custom ads \n<br />- Ability to exercise good judgment when interpreting instructions and to identify the strengths and weaknesses of alternative solutions \n<br />- Utilize strong written skills and bring effective visual ideas from concept through to completion<h2>Requirements</h2> - Working towards a BA or certificate from a Fine Arts program/Graphic Design school \n<br />- Experience with Adobe InDesign, and proficiency in Adobe Photoshop and Adobe Illustrator \n<br />- Knowledge of Mac OS and software upgrades and proficiency in Microsoft Office programs \n<br />- Must be a team player and flourish in a fast-paced, deadline-oriented environment \n<br />- Open to constructive feedback','Graphic Design Intern Virtual | Community Org| Equitable Justice','','publish','closed','closed','','graphic-design-intern-virtualcommunity-org-equitable-justice','','','2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1649',0,'noo_job','',0),(1650,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Community Org.','Community Org.','','publish','closed','closed','','community-org','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1651,30,'2018-04-05 00:00:00','2018-04-05 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Online since 1996 and a pioneer of online education, Anaheim University redefines the nature of online higher education, hiring acclaimed international professors and connecting them with students around the globe through live webcam classes. Interns would be responsible for assisting with the daily operation of administrative and student services tasks related to record-keeping for student services, administrative, and accreditation purposes. In addition, our interns will learn our intake and graduation processes, support university-wide federal and state compliance in all areas of operation, and learn from our experienced staff. \n<br /> \n<br />Anaheim University seeks interns who want to have a hands-on, project-oriented experience in their field. We can get our own coffee just fine, and our skills with the printer are top-notch already. Instead, we wan